description.narrative: By 2022, in UNICEF supported states, government and partner institutions have strengthened systems for multi-sector coordination, planning, monitoring, and human resource development for nutrition, which contributes to Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022

description.narrative: UNICEF supported POSHAN Abhiyaan (Nutrition Mission) in 2021 with renewed focus on child wasting. ;UNICEF and partners continued intensive advocacy and technical assistance for continuity of essential nutrition services following jointly developed “Commitment to Action for Nutrition” advocacy plan.; Government and development partners’ guidance, SBCC tools and other materials on COVID and nutrition, government directives and updated conditions were made publicly available on the POSHANCOVID19.in website and programmatic highlights shared through PoshanWeekly updates to 2,100 nutrition professionals. ;;UNICEF achieved results for children through convening partnerships leveraging human and financial resources across partners for better nutrition results for children. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:07/01/2022
